5-8f44-73ef7e85eba1", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-effective-development-co-operation-report-2014", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "cd47416ca155246f065269d21ab7bf04359d55c9a8fd62c789dd705b6ed6489b"}}, "hash": "856ad37e4ec52837d77aa724d69e93c8e0994581e281d25b291b9be9ebed8189", "text": "By 2000 this had fallen to 5%, and by 2012 to 3.4%. At the same time the number of countries for whom ODA was the primary international resource also fell. In 1990, ODA was the largest flow to 27 countries in the region \u2013 by 2011 this had fallen to 9 countries.27 6 of these countries are LDCs, and LDCs across the region continue to emphasise the need to meet the Monterrey targets, including donors allocating 0.7% GNI to ODA and providing ODA of 0.15% - 0.20% GNI to LDCs. In 2012, just 7 OECD donors reached the 0.15% target.28 In 2011 remittances were the largest resource flow to 12 Asia-Pacific countries; FDI was the largest for 9 countries. 26These figures are gross disbursements", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "42c4e573-f4fd-41ba-a6f7-9ae83faa67fc": {"__data__": {"id_": "42c4e573-f4fd-41ba-a6f7-9ae83faa67fc", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-effective-development-co-operation-report-2014", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Asia-Pacific Effective Development Co-operation Report 2014", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-effective